article.headline: Eastern Illinois 69, Jacksonville St. 65
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- With a game-high 28 points, Jake Byrne led Eastern Illinois to a 69-65 victory over Jacksonville State Thursday night. The score was tied 29-29 at the half and the lead changed hands nine times in the second half, but the Panthers (10-19, 6-13 Ohio Valley Conference) pulled ahead 62-61 with three minutes to go and didn't give it up again. Neither team led by more than eight points the whole game. Bobby Catchings was the only other double digit scorer for the Panthers with 17 points, and Ousmane Cisse had 12 rebounds. Courtney Bradley led the Gamecocks (8-21, 6-13 OVC) with 20 points. Will Ginn had 12 and Harold Crow and Erik Adams each added 11. The Panthers outrebounded the Gamecocks 41-26. Jacksonville State shot 42.6 percent from the floor while Eastern Illinois shot 42.3 percent.
